JOHANNESBURG, February 26 – Fifa on Thursday confirmed that Ace Ncobo will not stand for president in the upcoming SA Football Association (Safa) elections. Ncbobo was set to run against current Safa president Danny Jordaan for the top position at the local footballing body. FIFA representative Phillip Chiyangwa spoke at a press conference in Johannesburg on Thursday to make the announcement. “There has been an agreement to the dispute with Safa, and Ace Ncobo has confirmed he will not stand for Safa president,” said Chiyangwa. “Safa will elect an Electoral Committee before the elections can take place, so there will be no congress on March 24.” – African News Agency (ANA)